.SH NAME
init_phys_pg_pack_from_userptr \- initialize physical page pack from host memory
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" init_phys_pg_pack_from_userptr
.BI "(struct hl_ctx *ctx "  ","
.BI "struct hl_userptr *userptr "  ","
.BI "struct hl_vm_phys_pg_pack **pphys_pg_pack "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ctx" 12
pointer to the context structure.
.IP "userptr" 12
userptr to initialize from.
.IP "pphys_pg_pack" 12
result pointer.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function does the following:
- Pin the physical pages related to the given virtual block.
- Create a physical page pack from the physical pages related to the given
virtual block.
